<Author>LynB2
<Content>LITTLE GEM What a little gem! We found this hotel by surfing the net and would certainly recommend it. Really central, with the underground just round the corner in Gendarmenmarkt, a beautiful square with two churches and a concert hall. The bedrooms are clean and very comfortable, breakfast was good and the (all female) staff helpful and friendly. The area is surrounded by cafes and restaurants (try the Brasserie on the other side of the square), and the shops in the nearby arcade are to die for - try the food section of Galerie Lafayette! We will definitely stay here again on our next visit to Berlin. 
