<Author>A TripAdvisor Member
<Content>This is a lovely little hotel - - my favorite in Berlin I found this hotel quite by accident, looking for a good rate online. Previously in Berlin, I had stayed at the Hotel Unter den Linden, and found it to be satisfactory at best. It felt more like a pension than a hotel. So I lucked out and found Hotel Gendarm! It's a truly lovely hotel. My room really was more like a suite, with a separate sleeping area, and a small kitchen type arrangement. The views out the front of the Gendarmenmarkt are spectacular and it's close to everything, including the U-bahn, which is literally across the street. The windows are big and open easily. Everything was clean and in good working order. It's a small hotel, very quiet. They lock the door at night and you must use your key to get in the front door, but then again a lot of the smaller hotels in Europe are like that. The room service was wonderful and this was a very comfortable and nice hotel. I will definitely stay here again. I heard no noises at night, the bathroom was decent size. I didn't try the breakfast because I was feeling afraid to use my not-very-good German. Really nice hotel. 
